1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,050
The other extreme, the sensible way to retire, is the I'm-going-to-pitch-ride-in-and-start-fast method.

2
00:00:00,560 --> 00:00:05,409
One of my finest friends, Lou Gordon, has chosen this way to retire.

3
00:00:05,599 --> 00:00:13,409
Lou's retirement several years ago as a vice president of Atlanta's biggest bank was really commencement day for him.

4
00:00:13,599 --> 00:00:18,930
He established himself as a business consultant, and his pace is amazing.

5
00:00:19,359 --> 00:00:25,570
Now in his 60s, he serves numerous clients and is in national demand as a speaker.

6
00:00:26,240 --> 00:00:36,690
One of his special projects is helping to build Pi Sigma Epsilon, a young but fast-growing fraternity for professional salesmen and sales executives.

7
00:00:36,960 --> 00:00:39,730
Every time I see Lou, he seems younger.

8
00:00:39,839 --> 00:00:42,210
He's a young 30 in spirit.

9
00:00:42,560 --> 00:00:50,609
Few people I know of any age are reaping more from life than this senior citizen who resolved not to go out to pasture.

10
00:00:51,040 --> 00:00:57,409
And the Lou Gordons aren't the boring old grumps feeling sorry for themselves because they're old.

11
00:00:58,320 --> 00:01:03,490
Goals, intense goals, can keep a person alive when nothing else will.

12
00:01:03,839 --> 00:01:10,210
Mrs. D, the mother of a college friend of mine, contracted cancer when her son was only two.

13
00:01:10,560 --> 00:01:16,609
To darken matters, her husband had died only three months before her illness was diagnosed.

14
00:01:16,880 --> 00:01:21,648
Her physicians offered little hope, but Mrs. D would not give up.

15
00:01:21,760 --> 00:01:30,050
She was determined that she would see her two-year-old son through college by operating a small retail store left her by her husband.

16
00:01:30,400 --> 00:01:32,930
There were numerous surgical operations.

17
00:01:33,120 --> 00:01:37,250
Each time, the doctors would say, just a few more months.

18
00:01:37,920 --> 00:01:39,970
The cancer was never cured.

19
00:01:40,160 --> 00:01:43,889
But those few more months stretched into 20 years.

20
00:01:44,160 --> 00:01:47,010
She saw her son graduated from college.

21
00:01:47,200 --> 00:01:49,810
Six weeks later, she was gone.

22
00:01:50,560 --> 00:01:57,329
A goal, a burning desire, was powerful enough to stave off sure death for two decades.

23
00:01:58,240 --> 00:02:00,450
Use goals to live longer.

24
00:02:00,560 --> 00:02:11,330
No medicine in the world, and your physician will bear this out, is as powerful in bringing about long life as is the desire to do something.
